methods.of:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Construct a PartitionedTable as in of(Table, Set, String, TableDefinition, boolean), inferring
 most parameters as follows:
 
keyColumnNames
The names of all columns with a non-Table data type
constituentColumnName
The name of the first column with a Table data type
constituentDefinition
The TableDefinition of the value at the first cell in the constituent column. Consequently,
 table must be non-empty.
constituentChangesPermitted
The value of !table.isRefreshing()

*Overload 1*  
  :param table: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) - The "raw" table of tables. Should be refreshing if any constituents are.
  :param keyColumnNames: (java.util.Set<java.lang.String>) - The "key" column names from table. Key columns are used in
          PartitionedTable.transform(UnaryOperator) to validate the safety and correctness of join
          operations and in PartitionedTable.partitionedTransform(PartitionedTable, BinaryOperator) to
          correlate tables that should be transformed together. Passing an ordered set is highly recommended.
  :param constituentColumnName: (java.lang.String) - The "constituent" column name from table. The constituent column contains
          the underlying non-null tables that make up the result PartitionedTable.
  :param constituentDefinition: (io.deephaven.engine.table.TableDefinition) - A TableDefinition expected to be
          mutually compatible with all values in
          the "constituent" column of table
  :param constituentChangesPermitted: (boolean) - Whether table is permitted to report changes that impact the
          constituent column
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.PartitionedTable) A new PartitionedTable as described
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param table: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) - The "raw" table of tables
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.PartitionedTable) A new PartitionedTable as described
methods.ofTables:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Construct a Table with a single column containing the non-null values in constituents,
 and then use that to construct a PartitionedTable as in
 of(Table, Set, String, TableDefinition, boolean), inferring most parameters as follows:
 
keyColumnNames
An empty list
constituentColumnName
The single column containing non-null values from constituents
constituentChangesPermitted
false

*Overload 1*  
  :param constituentDefinition: (io.deephaven.engine.table.TableDefinition) - A TableDefinition expected to be
          mutually compatible with all values in
          the "constituent" column of table
  :param constituents: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table...) - The constituent tables to include. null values will be ignored.
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.PartitionedTable) A new PartitionedTable as described
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param constituents: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table...) - The constituent tables to include. null values will be ignored. At least one
          non-null constituent must be supplied.
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.PartitionedTable) A new PartitionedTable as described

text: Factory for producing Deephaven engine PartitionedTable instances.
